#Permutation - models
Would we observe an effect of pair type of this magnitude if mother–daughter labels were randomly assigned under the same social structure?

We can do a *label permutation*, --> Randomly reassign the “mother–daughter” labels among dyads, within year, while keeping the number of MD pairs per year fixed 

First, we can save the observed coefficients, for both models 
```{r}
#store coefficients
obs_coef_age_UA <- fixef(model_age_UA)$cond[c(
  "relation_age_c",
  "ultimate_pair_typemother-unrelated-daughter",
  "ultimate_pair_typemother-daughter",
  "colony_size"
)]

obs_coef_interaction_age_UA <- fixef(model_age_interaction_UA)$cond[c(
  "relation_age_c",
  "ultimate_pair_typemother-unrelated-daughter",
  "ultimate_pair_typemother-daughter",
  "colony_size",
  "relation_age_c:ultimate_pair_typemother-unrelated-daughter",
  "relation_age_c:ultimate_pair_typemother-daughter"
)]

```

*Label Permutations*
#### with interaction
```{r}
# Prepare storage
n_perm <- 50
perm_coefs_interaction_age_UA <- matrix(NA, nrow = n_perm, ncol = length(obs_coef_interaction_age_UA ))
colnames(perm_coefs_interaction_age_UA ) <- names(obs_coef_interaction_age_UA )

set.seed(123)

for (i in 1:n_perm) {
  # Permute pair_type2 within year
  perm_data_interaction <- edges_UA_final %>%
    group_by(year) %>%
    mutate(ultimate_pair_type = sample(ultimate_pair_type)) %>%
    ungroup()
  
  # Refit model
  perm_model_interaction_age_UA <- glmmTMB(weight_beta ~ relation_age_c * ultimate_pair_type + colony_size + unknown_age +
                              (1 | pairID) + (1 | year),
                              data = perm_data_interaction,
                              family = beta_family())
  
  # Save the coefficients of interest
  perm_coefs_interaction_age_UA[i, ] <- fixef(perm_model_interaction_age_UA)$cond[c(
  "relation_age_c",
  "ultimate_pair_typemother-unrelated-daughter",
  "ultimate_pair_typemother-daughter",
  "colony_size",
  "relation_age_c:ultimate_pair_typemother-unrelated-daughter",
  "relation_age_c:ultimate_pair_typemother-daughter"
  )]
}
# Convert to data frame
perm_coefs_df_interaction_age_UA <- as.data.frame(perm_coefs_interaction_age_UA)

save(perm_coefs_df_interaction_age_UA, file = here("results", "Q2_permutation_interaction_age_UA.RData"))
